// oracle-score (<PRODUCT>) — the TAO tolerance-aware LLM-ON scorer.
//
// Scores each ground-truth LAYER by its own TYPE, reusing the PRODUCT'S OWN
// deterministic authority and NEVER calling an LLM (C-DET-2):
//   DETERMINISTIC (exact)  — the proposal carries inputs through unchanged (no
//                            fabrication) and recompute/retrieve == expected
//                            bit-identically AND the product verifier accepts it.
//   STANDARD (set)         — every proposed value normalises into the product's
//                            allowed vocabulary (`<product>_oracle::reference`).
//   JUDGMENTAL (banded)    — soft distance to a reference; DIAGNOSTIC ONLY.
// Per-case PASS = DETERMINISTIC ∧ STANDARD. precision_pct = 100*passed/scored.
//
// This is a TEMPLATE: every `TODO(product)` hook must be filled with the
// product's real types + kernel + verifier before it compiles. Keep it LLM-free.

